[vc_row][vc_column width="7/12"][it_heading heading_style="style4" sub_weight="" gfont="" sgfont=""]Senior Software developer[/it_heading][vc_tta_accordion gap="3" c_position="right" active_section="1" shape="rounded" act_acc_t_color="#ffffff" act_acc_t_bg_color="#dd3333"][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-anchor" add_icon="true" title="Qualifications" tab_id="1446745132449-c46268ed-19dd"][vc_column_text]Recruitment consultant roles are generally open to graduates regardless of degree subject. Employers typically value drive, experience, skills and abilities as well as the determination to succeed over specific qualifications. Applying to an agency that specialises in a market or industry related to your degree subject, for example IT or engineering, may increase your chances. Entry with an HND or foundation degree is possible. Entry without a degree is possible for those with relevant experience, skills and abilities. Postgraduate study is not essential. You may find that relevant experience and skills are more useful.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-anchor" add_icon="true" title="Skills" tab_id="1446745179164-b42dc2d6-6d85"][vc_column_text]You will need to show evidence of the following:
  • excellent interpersonal and communication skills;
  • sales and negotiation skills;
  • a goal-orientated approach to work;
  • the ability to handle multiple priorities;
  • problem-solving ability;
  • the ability to meet deadlines and targets;
  • ambition and the determination to succeed;
  • tenacity;
  • confidence and self-motivation;
  • time management and organisational skills;
  • team-working skills;
  • creativity.
You must also enjoy working in a high-pressure environment and the responsibility that comes with it.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-bookmark-o" add_icon="true" title="Work experience" tab_id="1446745205972-c17d5dcc-4ae3"][vc_column_text]Work experience in sales, marketing or any customer-oriented role is useful for starting a career in the recruitment industry. Active membership of student societies may also help you provide evidence that you have the necessary skills.
